1
00:00:38,399 --> 00:00:39,359
Fatty!

2
00:00:39,479 --> 00:00:40,679
It's you again.

3
00:00:44,439 --> 00:00:45,600
Why is it spinning?

4
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:46,960
Why did it start spinning?

5
00:00:47,240 --> 00:00:48,439
The door closed.

6
00:01:04,879 --> 00:01:05,519
Shutong!

7
00:01:11,599 --> 00:01:12,319
Shutong!

8
00:01:27,799 --> 00:01:28,359
Shutong!

9
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:29,959
Give me your hand!

10
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:46,519
Chen Youxi!

11
00:01:50,159 --> 00:01:51,000
Chen Youxi!

12
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:53,400
Chen Youxi!

13
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:00,200
Chen Youxi!

14
00:02:26,159 --> 00:02:26,719
Old Lu!

15
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:29,919
Professor Lu!

16
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:34,120
Help me!

17
00:02:36,319 --> 00:02:38,199
Dawei, pull him up quickly!

18
00:02:39,759 --> 00:02:41,280
I... I...

19
00:02:43,719 --> 00:02:44,919
Professor Lu, you...

20
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:46,080
Don't let go!

21
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:48,000
I... I'm afraid of heights!

22
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:50,479
Old Lu!

23
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:57,520
Fatty!

24
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:58,319
Hurry!

25
00:02:58,960 --> 00:02:59,840
I... Lu...

26
00:03:06,159 --> 00:03:06,759
I...

27
00:03:09,439 --> 00:03:10,240
Professor Lu!

28
00:03:10,719 --> 00:03:11,639
Old Lu!

29
00:03:22,639 --> 00:03:23,520
You must be terrified.

30
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,919
I'm fine. Let's figure something out.

31
00:03:28,599 --> 00:03:29,319
We'll figure something out right now.

32
00:03:29,319 --> 00:03:30,719
The opposite platform is the safest.

33
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,680
Get ready. Come on.

34
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:14,520
It seems...

35
00:04:14,919 --> 00:04:16,519
...only those who pass this mechanism...

36
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:18,920
...can stop these spinning devices.

37
00:04:19,879 --> 00:04:20,800
That should be it.

38
00:04:22,279 --> 00:04:23,920
But according to the murals...

39
00:04:24,759 --> 00:04:25,759
...we are currently...

40
00:04:27,319 --> 00:04:28,720
...supposed to be treated as sacrifices...

41
00:04:28,759 --> 00:04:30,600
...and burned in the Great Cauldron.

42
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:31,839
Right.

43
00:04:32,439 --> 00:04:33,720
Then what is this place?

44
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:35,519
Where are Fatty and the others?

45
00:04:37,879 --> 00:04:38,680
Fatty!

46
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:42,519
Old Lu!

47
00:04:43,879 --> 00:04:44,680
Ding Dawei!

48
00:04:45,319 --> 00:04:46,439
Can you hear me?

49
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:48,319
What's going on?

50
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,920
Could they be in danger?

51
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:50,639
No.

52
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:53,079
With Fatty's skills, he should be fine.

53
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,240
It might be because these stone steles...

54
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:56,399
...are blocking the sound.

55
00:04:57,839 --> 00:04:59,360
We'd better find a way out.

56
00:05:16,959 --> 00:05:17,519
Professor Lu!

57
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:21,439
Professor Lu!

58
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:39,160
Professor Lu!

59
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,759
Fatty, be careful.

60
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,639
There's an eyeball pattern here.

61
00:06:23,279 --> 00:06:24,319
I have one here too.

62
00:06:29,319 --> 00:06:31,959
Could there be a mechanism to get out?

63
00:06:32,199 --> 00:06:34,360
If we think according to the murals...

64
00:06:35,439 --> 00:06:36,560
...if there is a mechanism...

65
00:06:36,959 --> 00:06:38,959
...it leads to the next sacrifice step.

66
00:06:39,519 --> 00:06:42,079
You mean burning the sacrifices?

67
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:43,360
Right.

68
00:07:02,439 --> 00:07:03,079
Wait a minute.

69
00:07:50,079 --> 00:07:51,720
This is the Great Cauldron from the murals.

70
00:07:51,839 --> 00:07:52,360
Exactly.

71
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:53,920
This matches the content on the murals.

72
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,000
I'll send you down first.

73
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:57,519
One, two, three.

74
00:08:01,639 --> 00:08:02,360
Are you okay?

75
00:08:02,399 --> 00:08:03,160
I'm fine.

76
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,000
Old Lu!

77
00:08:23,399 --> 00:08:24,319
Old Lu!

78
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:34,759
Professor Lu!

79
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:41,159
Old Lu!

80
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:44,840
Old Lu!

81
00:08:47,559 --> 00:08:48,240
Old Lu!

82
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:49,759
Old Lu!

83
00:08:53,639 --> 00:08:54,120
What's wrong?

84
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,759
Old Lu! Old Lu!

85
00:08:56,159 --> 00:08:57,600
Old Lu! Old Lu!

86
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:58,320
Old Lu!

87
00:09:00,639 --> 00:09:01,720
Wake up, Old Lu!

88
00:09:03,279 --> 00:09:05,000
Did you hurt yourself when you fell?

89
00:09:05,639 --> 00:09:06,679
I didn't.

90
00:09:06,799 --> 00:09:08,440
I was just floating down,

91
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:10,759
and I felt my butt...

92
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:13,159
something was poking me.

93
00:09:13,159 --> 00:09:14,879
Then I took a look,

94
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:17,919
and there was a skull this big!

95
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,440
It scared me to death!

96
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,480
So I figured I'd just lie down.

97
00:09:22,919 --> 00:09:23,759
Is it this one?

98
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:30,039
W-w-what is the meaning of this?

99
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,639
Is this a slaughterhouse backyard?

100
00:09:32,399 --> 00:09:33,240
This should be where the Dian King

101
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:34,960
held sacrificial ceremonies.

102
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:36,960
Wait.

103
00:09:38,679 --> 00:09:39,399
Listen.

104
00:10:04,919 --> 00:10:06,159
Red-backed toads!

105
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:08,480
Why is it these things again?

106
00:10:08,639 --> 00:10:09,600
Go, go, go!

107
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:10,240
Hurry!

108
00:10:14,399 --> 00:10:15,519
You three go find the mechanism.

109
00:10:15,519 --> 00:10:16,559
We'll hold them off here.

110
00:10:16,799 --> 00:10:17,600
Okay, okay, okay.

111
00:10:18,399 --> 00:10:19,840
Professor Lu, h-here!

112
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,039
Professor Lu!

113
00:10:33,159 --> 00:10:34,080
There are two dragon heads here.

114
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:35,120
Dragon heads! Dragon heads!

115
00:10:36,159 --> 00:10:36,799
Pull!

116
00:10:37,279 --> 00:10:37,840
Pull!

117
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:38,519
Pull!

118
00:10:57,279 --> 00:10:58,399
The door is open! Hurry!

119
00:10:58,639 --> 00:10:59,200
We found it!

120
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,279
Go, go, go!

121
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:05,519
Hurry!

122
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:07,720
Shutong!

123
00:11:08,399 --> 00:11:09,399
Hurry! Hurry, Shutong!

124
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:11,399
Brother!

125
00:11:11,399 --> 00:11:12,360
The door is closing! Hurry!

126
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:13,080
Hurry up!

127
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,000
That scared me to death.

128
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,600
Thanks to Advisor He.

129
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:22,799
Both brave and smart.

130
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,279
What is that?

131
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:25,879
I don't know.

132
00:11:26,159 --> 00:11:27,279
I just saw it in the mechanism.

133
00:11:27,279 --> 00:11:28,080
Open it and see.

134
00:11:44,960 --> 00:11:46,799
Could this be the structural map of the Ming Lou?

135
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:47,720
Old Lu.

136
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,519
The dragon's aura is formless;

137
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,919
the corpse transcends to become immortal.

138
00:11:57,399 --> 00:11:58,080
Look.

139
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:00,639
There seems to be light over there.

140
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:09,240
Looks like we're saved.

141
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:10,519
Let's study it outside. Go!

142
00:12:10,519 --> 00:12:11,480
Go, go, go!

143
00:12:22,399 --> 00:12:23,279
Look!

144
00:12:24,159 --> 00:12:25,039
Water Dragon Vortex!

145
00:12:30,519 --> 00:12:31,440
Is there any place

146
00:12:31,519 --> 00:12:33,679
that looks more like the entrance to the Dian King's tomb?

147
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:40,759
What's happening?

148
00:12:40,759 --> 00:12:41,679
An earthquake?

149
00:12:41,759 --> 00:12:43,639
Why do we run into all the bad luck?

150
00:12:43,639 --> 00:12:44,720
Look at the water surface.

151
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:47,559
Why is there a vortex on the water?

152
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:49,960
I get it!

153
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:51,759
Why are you so startled? What do you get?

154
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:52,600
Don't interrupt.

155
00:12:53,039 --> 00:12:53,960
Let me tell you,

156
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,279
on the back of the thing

157
00:12:55,279 --> 00:12:56,759
we found inside the Ming Lou,

158
00:12:56,759 --> 00:12:58,000
wasn't it written there?

159
00:12:58,240 --> 00:12:59,559
The dragon's aura is formless.

160
00:12:59,919 --> 00:13:01,440
Without a cataclysm,

161
00:13:01,919 --> 00:13:04,080
it is impossible for outsiders to breach.

162
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:07,360
It fits this scene perfectly.

163
00:13:07,559 --> 00:13:08,840
Old Lu is right.

164
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:10,039
Without a cataclysm,

165
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:11,720
it is impossible for outsiders to breach.

166
00:13:11,799 --> 00:13:12,559
It probably refers to

167
00:13:12,559 --> 00:13:14,759
this special natural phenomenon.

168
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:17,360
Those villagers are coming again!

169
00:13:17,559 --> 00:13:18,279
What do we do?

170
00:13:19,879 --> 00:13:21,679
Come quick! They're here!

171
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:31,279
Where did they go?

172
00:13:31,679 --> 00:13:32,879
They haven't gone far.

173
00:13:33,039 --> 00:13:35,360
Split up and find them!

174
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:12,159
I'm exhausted.

175
00:14:57,679 --> 00:14:58,519
Professor Lu.

176
00:14:59,559 --> 00:15:00,559
I've always been curious.

177
00:15:01,399 --> 00:15:02,480
You risk your lives,

178
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:03,960
but what's the point of archaeology?

179
00:15:05,320 --> 00:15:07,039
Take our current trip, for example.

180
00:15:07,279 --> 00:15:08,559
The Ancient Kingdom of Dian

181
00:15:08,559 --> 00:15:11,360
is a lost civilization.

182
00:15:12,759 --> 00:15:14,000
What we're doing this time

183
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:17,600
is like opening a window to this civilization.

184
00:15:35,279 --> 00:15:37,000
One, two, three!

185
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:46,320
There's nothing here.

186
00:15:47,879 --> 00:15:48,600
Fatty.

187
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,399
Isn't there still one box left unopened?

188
00:15:58,480 --> 00:15:59,240
Open it.

189
00:16:01,879 --> 00:16:03,799
One, two, three!
